
ğŸ“¬ No-Code Email Filter App

A no-code system for blocking unwanted emails, filtering newsletters, and managing inbox rules using modern automation tools.

ğŸ”§ Tech Stack
Category	Tools Used
Frontend	AppSheet
Backend / Database	Google Sheets
Automation	Make
Email Provider	Gmail
ğŸ¯ Project Overview

This project solves a common problem: email overload. Most inboxes are full of newsletters, promos, and repeated senders that make it hard to focus on important messages.

This no-code app allows users to:

Block specific senders

Filter out certain types of emails

Auto-delete or archive messages

View activity logs

Manage filters through an easy-to-use AppSheet UI

The system runs fully automated through Make and stores structured data in Google Sheets.

ğŸ§© System Architecture
1. User Interface (AppSheet)

Users submit blocked senders or filtering rules

Can view logs of what emails were filtered

Fully mobile-friendly UI

2. Database (Google Sheets)

Contains the following tables:

Blocked Senders

Filter Rules

Email Logs

Settings

3. Automation Layer (Make)

Scenario includes:

Gmail Watcher

Google Sheets Lookup / Update

Logic filters

Action modules (delete, archive, apply label)

4. Email Source (Gmail)

Make reads and processes incoming messages through the Gmail API.

